President Muhammadu Buhari will, at 7pm today (Sunday 29th March, 2020), address Nigerians. The broadcast may not be unconnected with developments relating to the COVID-19 pandemic and calls by Nigerians for the President to speak to the nation. The Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Mr. Femi Adesina, disclosed Buhari’s 7pm broadcast in a statement on Sunday. “Television, radio and other electronic media are enjoined to hook up to the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority (NTA) and Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria (FRCN), respectively, for the broadcast,” he said. 